title: Why I like Facebook

Facebook has given me the opportunity to connect to the joys and sadness of friends and family. I have a physical condition that keeps me at home most of the time. Facebook has given me the opportunity to connect in ways that I would not be able to. I also enjoy connecting with people that I do not know who have the same interest that I do. I love seeing other peopleâ€™s artwork, sewing, creativity of all kinds. I love reading stories, especially those heartwarming stories that so often come across
In the Facebook feed. Iâ€™m able to share pictures of my grandchildren as they grow with people that I have known since  I was a teenager. I grew up on an island where most people knew each other, and we have stayed in touch through Facebook. Iâ€™ve watched their children and their grandchildren. Iâ€™ve listened to their sorrows as they have lost loved ones and tried to comfort them as they have tried to comfort me many times.
